    "department": "Sales",
    "description": "About Whippy\nWhippy helps businesses grow without adding headcount by combining messaging, automation, AI agents, and VoIP into one unified workspace. Companies use Whippy to communicate with customers, automate workflows, and deploy AI-powered teammates for recruiting, sales, and support. We’re a fast-moving, bootstrapped AI company used by 1,000+ businesses — from national staffing agencies to modern pharmacies — and we’re scaling quickly.\n\nWhy This Internship Is Worth Your Time\nThis isn’t a “fetch coffee and fix a spreadsheet” internship. You’ll work directly with serial founders who have built companies from zero to millions in revenue, earned press in major publications, and helped interns go on to launch their own funded startups or land roles at high-growth companies. If you want to see how an AI startup is actually built — from sales to strategy — this will be the closest seat to the action you’ll get.\n\n\nThis internship is structured as a learning experience with hands-on training and mentorship; there is no expectation of employment at the end of the term.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\n - Manage real sales operations tasks under direct supervision.\n\n - Keep HubSpot organized by cleaning data, updating CRM fields, and ensuring strong pipeline hygiene.\n\n - Pull targeted prospect lists and support outbound efforts across industries.\n\n - Research new verticals, competitors, and market opportunities.\n\n - Help create dashboards, reports, and insights that guide decision-making.\n\n - Support workflow documentation and internal processes as we scale.\n\n - Optional exposure to strategy calls, founder meetings, and customer conversations.\n   \n   Note: All responsibilities are designed to be educational and training-focused.\n\nWhat You’ll Learn\n\n - How real startups scale revenue from thousands to millions.\n\n - How Go-To-Market teams operate: SDR workflows, AE pipelines, list building, data cleanup, forecasting, and sales automation.\n\n - How founders think about growth, product, and prioritization.\n\n - How to use tools like HubSpot, Apollo, LinkedIn Sales Navigator, and internal AI systems.\n\nWho This Is Perfect For\n\n - Currently enrolled in a bachelor’s or master’s program and looking to gain real-world experience directly from founders.\n\n - Curious, hungry, and interested in business development, sales operations, or SaaS.\n\n - Someone who wants a portfolio of real work, not theoretical classroom projects.\n\n - A self-starter who wants exposure to a high-growth AI environment.\n\nWhy Interns Love Working With Us\nWe don’t treat you like an intern.\nYou get ownership of projects.\nYou’re in the room for real discussions.\nAnd you leave with skills and experience that open doors — whether your future is startups, consulting, VC, or creating something of your own.\n\nSchedule\n2–3 days per week\nHybrid, with at least 1 in-office day in Culver City or West Hollywood\n\nCompensation\nThis internship is unpaid or stipend-based (depending on school credit requirements). It is designed primarily for training, education, and real-world exposure to the operations of a high-growth AI company.",
